article.description: S. Alabama snaps skid, beats UL-Lafayette 81-73
article.headline: S. Alabama snaps skid, beats UL-Lafayette 81-73
article.linkText: S. Alabama snaps skid, beats UL-Lafayette 81-73
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. -- Augustine Rubit scored 21 points and went 7 of 10 from the field as South Alabama snapped a six-game losing streak and held on for an 81-73 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Thursday night. Ken Williams added 18 points, Aakim Saintil 15 and Antoine Allen 12 for South Alabama (7-11, 1-4 Sun Belt), which shot 59.2 percent from the field. The Rajin' Cajuns (11-6, 2-2) went on a late 11-3 run to cut their deficit to 69-67 with 2:23 left, but South Alabama then scored eight straight points. Louisiana-Lafayette shot 38.7 percent from the field and had 12 shots blocked by the Jaguars. Rubit accounted for five of the blocks. Elfrid Payton led Louisiana-Lafayette with 18 points while Shawn Long added 15.
